               <desc type="building-data" xml:lang="en">
                  <p>Emerald Wave Bridge, also called Mt. Tai Bridge. Original date of construction unknown. A bridge appears in this location on Gao Ruxing's Jinci zhitu and may have been built at the same time as the Taishan Temple, prior to 1342. It is labeled Taishan Bridge on the Qian-long painting of the site. This structure is number 39 on our plan of the site.</p>
